Rift Valley fever - Somalia 980123225815

Date: Mon, 20 Jul 1998 15:44:22 -0700
Source: The Nation, Nairobi, 8 Jul 1998
Via: Dorothy Preslar <dpreslar@fas.org>

Basil Criticos, Health Assistant Minister, said on 7 July that nine deaths
in the Tana River District were caused by Rift Valley fever. A medical team
has been sent to the area to investigate the problem. A report will be
forthcoming from Coast Provincial Medical Officer of Health, Dr. S.K. Shariff.
--
ProMED-mail
e-mail: promed@usa.healthnet.org
[Some years ago it was demonstrated in Kenya that Rift Valley Fever
outbreaks followed rains that managed to fill the dhambos, or shallow
normally dry sloughs/slews, where the mosquito vector eggs are laid. -
Mod.MHJ
